    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lacquerware formed on clay, plaster and wooden bodies, on which grass or silk cloth and raw lacquer are mounted layer by layer for drying, before the original form is removed, leaving the shaped lacquered cloth. This is then polished, and decorated with more lacquer, paint, or otherwise.</Note_Text>
